{"questionId":"27892","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Gen is investigating the relationship between two sets of data, labelled <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi></math>, that&nbsp;she collected. She created a scatter plot with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> on the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mn>10</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mi>Q</mi></math> on the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis.&nbsp;Gen noticed that the points had a strong linear correlation, so she drew a line of best fit,&nbsp;as shown in the diagram. The line passes through the points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>14</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/a2f1dd4bd7b7c006f143231b395e8781d944644d.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find an equation for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Gradient&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>14</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mn>10</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mi>P</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mi>P</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0501</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mi>P</mi></mrow></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0501187</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>7</mn><mi>P</mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27892","referenceCode":"22N.1.AHL.TZ0.13a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find an equation for Q in terms of P.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.10—Scaling large numbers, log-log graphs","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.8—Use of technology to solve systems of linear equations and polynomial equations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}